videos.description: Matt Farrell zips a pass between defenders to Martinas Geben for a strong two-handed jam.
videos.headline: Notre Dame's Geben throws down two-handed dunk

videos.description: Jeremie Tyler knocks the ball away then gets the assist on the other end with a pass to Taylor Persons.
videos.headline: Tyler, Persons give Ball State its first lead

videos.description: Sean Sellers swoops in and grabs the offensive rebound for a bucket as Ball State takes a 21-15 lead over Notre Dame in the first half.
videos.headline: Sellers cleans up miss for easy putback

videos.description: Martinas Geben gets the ball deep in the post and hits a turnaround hook right hook for a chance at a 3-point play
videos.headline: Geben's strong move in the post draws 3-point play

videos.description: Bonzie Colson chases down an offensive rebound, but flips head first over Ball State's bench.
videos.headline: Colson goes over Ball State's bench on rebound attempt

videos.description: Bonzie Colson throws down an emphatic two-handed dunk off an outlet pass from Rex Pflueger.
videos.headline: Notre Dame's defense leads to Colson dunk

videos.description: Rex Pflueger opens up the second half with an aggressive move to the basket for a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Pflueger starts second half with acrobatic and-1

videos.description: Bonzie Colson strips the ball and takes it himself for a finger roll to put Notre Dame back on top.
videos.headline: Colson goes coast-to-coast with steal and layup

videos.description: Tayler Persons brings up the ball and takes advantage of a mismatch for a jumper to put Ball State ahead by nine points.
videos.headline: Persons gets friendly roll

videos.description: TJ Gibbs drains a 3-pointer off a nice pass from Matt Farrell to cut Notre Dame's deficit to three points.
videos.headline: Gibbs' 3-pointer cuts deficit in half

videos.description: Tayler Persons uses the screen and knocks down the 3-pointer with a hand in his face as Ball State upsets Notre Dame 80-77.
videos.headline: Persons hits game-winning 3-pointer to upset No.9 Notre Dame.
